<div><h3>SPAN 141 - Spanish Translation Workshop </h3>  <hr>Introduces students to issues and practices of translation including aspects of cultural differences, translation deficiencies and approaches to source texts. Students will work on projects in the community, including translation and/or interpreting. Among the translations will be prose, poetry, songs, ads, editorials, government legal, financial and health forms.<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=29&coid=98536" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=98536&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=98536&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt1032" target="_blank">SPAN 131</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span> &amp; <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=29&coid=99858" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=99858&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=99858&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt8517" target="_blank">SPAN 132</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span> <br><br><strong>Course Designation/Attribute:</strong> POP<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Offered periodically<br><br><strong>Placement Guidelines</strong><br> Please visit the <a href="http://www.clarku.edu/departments/foreign/undergraduate/placement.cfm" target="_blank">Department of Language, Literature and Culture</a> for the language placement guidelines.<br><br><div style="display: none; z-index: 1000;" class="tooltip for_tt1032"></div><div style="display: none; z-index: 1000;" class="tooltip for_tt8517"></div></div>		</td>
